content:
When working with 3D models in Panda3D, you may need to replace specific materials across different parts of a model. For example, after loading a car model, you might want to change all instances of a "blueMetal" material to a newly defined red material. The `replaceMaterial` method allows you to dynamically update all occurrences of one material with another throughout the entire model, ensuring consistent visual changes without manually reassigning materials to each part.

car.replaceMaterial(blue, red)

cpp

PT(Material) blue = car.find_material("blueMetal");
PT(Material) red = new Material;
//...set up red material

car.replace_material(blue, red);

Related Classes

